Defendant Kevin A Blum in court with attorney Darryl E. Smith.  Jesica Ann Ballenger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the state, the Court ordered Count 2 DISMISSED. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, Barbara S., and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 4 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 YEARS.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Corrections with release privileges for work and treatment only for the first 6 months (No electronic monitoring); for the balance of time the defendant shall have work, treatment, and electronic monitoring.  Electronic monitoring permitted only if adhering to rules during condition time-state objects to electronic monitoring.  Goodtime allowed.  
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers/houses);
*Cooperate with all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school with part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;

The Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $2400.00 plus all mandatory applicable costs, penalties, surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge by the end of probation period- bail to apply.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan; cooperate with any treatment recommended.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 30 months.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 30 months.  If revoked, the Court ordered that all financial obligations  be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.
Filed;
-Driver Safety Plan;
-Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence- copy to defendant.
